d workers are to extend coverage through re-allocating the benefits given to higher-level workers, maintain the benefits of the well-off as the number of outsiders continues to grow, or simply ignore the problem. This book asks why different nations have taken different tacks in handling-or not handling-this problem.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 30. Aug 2021) 0aWelfare statezEurope. 4aPolitics and Government. 4aSocial and Political Sciences. 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / Political Economy.2bisacsh  adualisation, social policy, benefit access, party politics, public opinion.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package 2016-2018z978311066731808iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017z978311060644708iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertAmsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017z978311066284940uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9789048529391zCo-access DOI >> click Walter de Gruyter40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9789048529391423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9789048529391.jpg  a978-3-11-060644-7  AUP eBook Package Backlist 2015-2017c2015d2017  a978-3-11-066284-9  Amsterdam University Press Complete eBook-Package 2017b2017  a978-3-11-066731-8  AUP eBook Package 2016-2018c2016d2018  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aEBA_STMALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles  aPDA11SSHE  aPDA12STME  aPDA13ENGE  aPDA17SSHEE  aPDA5EBK